==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Diluvium
<hw>Di*lu"vi*um</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>; <plu><it>pl.</it> E.
<plw>Diluviums</plw> <pr>(#)</pr>, L. <plw>Diluvia</plw>
<pr>(#)</pr>.</plu> <ety>[L. <ets>diluvium</ets>. See <er>Dilute</er>,
<er>Deluge</er>.]</ety> <fld>(Geol.)</fld> <def>A deposit of superficial
loam, sand, gravel, stones, etc., caused by former action of flowing
waters, or the melting of glacial ice.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><note>⟦hand⟧ The accumulation of matter by the ordinary operation of
water is termed <xex>alluvium</xex>.</note>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

